Ultrasonic Schematic Sketch (Acoustic Resonator – Easiest to Build & Test)
Goal: A handheld ultrasonic "tube" using a piezo transducer (40–200 kHz common range) driven by Arduino/Teensy PWM. OPEN = strong resonance tone/vibration, CLOSED = silent/gated off. Decay m fades the envelope (like lifetime in cosmic bands). Shear modulates frequency slightly for "drift".
Core Components (total ~$15–30):
Microcontroller: Arduino Nano / Uno / Teensy 4.x (for fast PWM & computation)
Piezo transducer: 40 kHz cleaning type or 100–200 kHz medical/cleaning (e.g., 16–60 mm dia, 10–60 W rating)
MOSFET: Logic-level N-channel (IRL540 / IRLZ44N / BSS138 for low power)
Resistor: 100–220 Ω gate, optional 10–100 Ω series with piezo
Inductor (optional boost): 1–10 mH for resonant peaking (higher voltage swing)
Power: 5–12 V battery/USB (higher V = louder, but watch piezo rating)
Optional: Op-amp (LM358) for envelope control, small speaker/mic for audible feedback
